{"info": {"author": "Jiang Yi Xin", "author_email": "15221613915@163.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Science/Research", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6"], "description": "# Flask Api Resource\n\n> package flask to use conveniently like django\n\n# Usage\n\n## Step 1\n\n```python\nfrom flask import Flask\nfrom flask_api_resource import FlaskApiResource\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\napp.config['INSTALL_APPS'] = []  # your application app like user\napi = FlaskApiResource()\napi.init_app(app=app)  # this can auto scan your resource\n```\n\n## Step 2\nAccording to your logic to create different app\n\n```text\nuser\n    __init__.py\n    apis\n        user.py\n```\n\n```python\n# user.py\nfrom flask_api_resource.api import BaseResource\nfrom flask_api_resource.decorator import get\n\nclass UserResource(BaseResource):\n    \n    def get_urls(self):\n        return [\n            ('/detail', self.detail)\n        ]\n    \n    @get\n    def detail(self):\n        return self.success({'id': 1})\n```\n\n```python\n# __init__.py\n\ndef register(api):\n    from .apis.user import UserResource\n    api.register(UserResource)\n```\n\n## Step 3\n\nrun the Flask app server and open the http://127.0.0.1:5000/rest/user/detail", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/jiangyx3915/flask-ap-resource", "keywords": "", "license": "MPL-2.0", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "flask-api-resource", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/flask-api-resource/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/flask-api-resource/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/jiangyx3915/flask-ap-resource"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/flask-api-resource/0.1.2/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "package flask to use conveniently like django", "version": "0.1.2", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Flask Api Resource</h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>package flask to use conveniently like django</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h1>Usage</h1>\n<h2>Step 1</h2>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">flask</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Flask</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">flask_api_resource</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">FlaskApiResource</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">app</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Flask</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"vm\">__name__</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s1\">'INSTALL_APPS'</span><span class=\"p\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">[]</span>  <span class=\"c1\"># your application app like user</span>\n<span class=\"n\">api</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">FlaskApiResource</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"n\">api</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">init_app</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>  <span class=\"c1\"># this can auto scan your resource</span>\n</pre>\n<h2>Step 2</h2>\n<p>According to your logic to create different app</p>\n<pre>user\n    __init__.py\n    apis\n        user.py\n</pre>\n<pre><span class=\"c1\"># user.py</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">flask_api_resource.api</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">BaseResource</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">flask_api_resource.decorator</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">get</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">class</span> <span class=\"nc\">UserResource</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">BaseResource</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n    \n    <span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">get_urls</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n        <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span>\n            <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'/detail'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">detail</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">]</span>\n    \n    <span class=\"nd\">@get</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">detail</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n        <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">success</span><span class=\"p\">({</span><span class=\"s1\">'id'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">})</span>\n</pre>\n<pre><span class=\"c1\"># __init__.py</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">register</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">api</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n    <span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">.apis.user</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">UserResource</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">api</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">register</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">UserResource</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<h2>Step 3</h2>\n<p>run the Flask app server and open the <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:5000/rest/user/detail\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://127.0.0.1:5000/rest/user/detail</a></p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6821533, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "598e9b6cdd3fbfd3116792944a8c61e8", "sha256": "fe2bf0cb5d4453b359fcf1e88fda056ecfe11db30543439e79ed2b7a8b87d443